onto mixing bowl lid, until sauce has thickened. Serve warm with coconut roti and lime wedges."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Coconut Roti","content":["350 g plain flour","200 g fresh grated coconut flesh (see Tips)","½ - 1 tsp salt, to taste","2 tbsp oil, plus extra for frying","100 g lukewarm water"]},{"title":"Kuruma iraichchi","content":["750 g chuck steak, cut into cubes (3 cm)","2 tsp salt","2 - 4 tsp ground black pepper","1 tbsp ground coriander","2 tsp ground cumin","1 tsp fennel seeds","3 garlic cloves","1 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","3 - 5 fresh bird's eye chillies, trimmed and deseeded if preferred","2 brown onions, cut into quarters","½ tsp ground turmeric","8 fresh curry leaves","2 pandan leaves, tied into a knot","2 tbsp white wine vinegar","1 stalk fresh lemongrass, cut into halves","1 tbsp tomato paste","270 g thick coconut cream","1 tbsp ghee","1 lime, cut into wedges, to serve"]}],"id":"r115165","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-DiIAIGPvtmE\/XZQv9Icw_hI\/AAAAAAAAchU\/icYalMOXevQgbjKA2GOQUHWH61uR97PyACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_PxjAERzOGpE2z9uB.png","title":"Kuruma iraichchi with coconut roti","publishedAt":"2016-07-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"38 g","fat":"41 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"47.6 g","calories":"3054 kJ \/ 727 kcal"},"usefulItems":"silicone bread mat, rolling pin, kitchen towel, large frying pan, thermal serving bowl or plate, bowl, small bowl , stove top","hintsAndTricks":["You can purchase fresh coconut at most supermarkets or fruit and vegetable stores.","For a milder curry, reduce the number of chillies and deseed before using.","To save time, prepare coconut roti up to step 2 and set aside, then continue with recipe. Fry roti in step 9 when Kuruma iraichchi is cooking. Cover to keep warm and set aside until Kuruma iraichchi is ready to serve.","Coconut roti can be prepared a day ahead and reheated in a warm oven before serving.","To save time, use store-bought roti and start recipe on step 4."],"basicInfo":